---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 217
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Death=The Art of Dying
By: Phadampa Sangay
Format: Verse
---
Even on one’s birthday morning, omens of one’s death appear;
Ever be alert and watchful; waste no time, O Tingri folk. ...
Ever transient is this world of ours; all things change and pass away;
For a distant journey even now prepare, O Tingri folk.
